node.text: Our first ever YouTuber awards show where we celebrate those in the YouTube fishing world for what they do best.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'FISHING RIDDLE Four men were fishing in a boat on the lake. The boat turned over and all four men fell in the lake. And yet, not one single man got wet. How can this be?'.

node.text: COMMENT what you think the answer is 🧠🧠🧠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 19, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: Those nail clippers cut through anything, I swear! Who else uses these to cut line on the boat?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 19, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text: How's your summer going, you get a BINGO yet? 👀👀

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4 WAYS TO BE A BETTER NET MAN 1. Have the net ready to go nearby, not tangled up in some fishing line. 2. Give your buddy enough room to fight the fish. Stay off to the side. 3. Don't rush the landing. Let the rod do most of the work, try not to chase the fish with the net. 4. Don't lunge forward and stab the fish, instead, use a scooping motion.'.

node.text: Does your net man do these things?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 17, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and nature.

node.text: A chunky Newport, Rhode Island striper! Who else has been fishing in this area?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 16, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text: You know the answer 😎

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Karl's FISHING 101: Spook MAKE SURE YOU SAVE IT'.

node.text: Get to know this classic lure! When do you like to throw spooks?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Karl's FISHING 101: Spook MAKE SURE YOU SAVE IT'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'HISTORY In the early 1900's James Heddon, of the Heddon Lure Company, simply cut off the end of a wooden broom stick, attached two hooks and found a new way to catch fish. In 1939, the plastic version was engineered, and was named the Zara Spook.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'WHAT IS IT? A classic topwater lure that is meant to mimic injured fish. It has a long hard body (usually minnow shap) and two treble hooks. Nowadays there are countless versions of the spook that come in many sizes, so you can catch everything from panfish to a tuna.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 15, 2021. May be an image of body of water and text that says 'HOW TO FISH IT The spook has no action of its own. The action is created by the angler, but don't let that stop you from using it, because this lure lands biggins! Try these retrieves: -Walk the dog Short quick rod snaps Single twitch with long pause'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'WHERE TO FISH IT Spooks work in almost every situation. Even if fish are far away or deep, the erratic action you create with the lure can call them over. One great time to fish them is when you're around baitfish. So if you see bait busting on the surface or birds bomb-diving, throw a spook in that area.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'SET UP Almost any set up will work with the spook, it comes down to preference with this lure. However, try to to use mono or braid for your line since they float. A sinking line can effect the action.'.
Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'EAT ME'.

node.text: Who likes to fish in the rain?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3 RAIN TIPS'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 13, 2021. May be an image of body of water and text that says '1. CONDITIONS If it's not cold outside and the bite is on, fishing in the rain is really fun! "I'm always wet. What is rain?" But if you see lightning, go inside so your rod doesn't get fried. This is my official warning to you!'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '2. STAND OUT Rain usually means darker skies, a lot of distrubance on the surface water, and the water muddying up. Lean towards using baits with a lot of vibration and movement! You'll also want to try super contrasting colors like chartreuse or. black'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on July 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3. FIND CURRENTS Currents pick up when its raining so go where the waters flowing cause its probably pushing baitfish there. Try these: -Drains Feeder creeks Runoff areas'.
